article.description: — Charles Manning Jr. hit three of four at the free throw line in the final 22 seconds to seal South Alabama's 73-67 win over Georgia Southern on Saturday.
article.headline: South Alabama holds off Georgia Southern, wins 73-67
article.linkText: South Alabama holds off Georgia Southern, wins 73-67
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. -- — Charles Manning Jr. hit three of four at the free throw line in the final 22 seconds to seal South Alabama's 73-67 win over Georgia Southern on Saturday. Javon Franklin and Manning each scored 19 points and Jay Jay Chandler added 12 points to lead South Alabama (12-5, 2-2 Sun Belt). Georgia Southern (8-7, 1-3) rallied from a 13-point halftime deficit Elijah McCadden came off the Eagles' bench to score 19 points and grab 11 rebounds. Gedi Juozapaitis added 10 points and four assists. ------ https://www.espn.com/mens-college-basketball/boxscore/--/gameId/401371139 AP college basketball: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and https://twitter.com/AP--Top25
